1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,440
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:04,520
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,520 --> 00:00:05,520
And my name is Katherine.
我是Katherine。

4
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:09,000
And today at EnglishPod, we have a lesson for you about small talk.
今天在EnglishPod，我们为大家准备了一节关于闲聊的课程。

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,000
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,280
We continue with our series about short casual conversations you may have with your friends,
我们继续这个系列，内容是关于你和朋友、

7
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:18,600
somebody you haven't seen in a long time, or maybe even a co-worker.
很久没见的人，甚至可能是同事之间进行的简短随意对话。

8
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:19,600
That's right.
没错。

9
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,000
So in today's dialogue, we're going to listen to two people who work in the same building.
所以在今天的对话中，我们会听到两个在同一栋楼工作的人。

10
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,760
They're going to talk a little bit about travel, right Marco?
他们会聊一点旅行的事，对吧，Marco？

11
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:27,760
Yeah.
是的。

12
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:31,960
And a little bit about recommending a place to go on vacation, maybe Europe.
还会推荐一个度假的地方，可能是欧洲。

13
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:36,880
And so we're going to have some great phrases as to speaking of this topic very briefly
我们会学到一些很棒的短语，用来和朋友

14
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:37,880
with a friend.
简短地聊这个话题。

15
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:38,880
All right.
好的。

16
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,880
Let's listen to today's dialogue.
让我们来听今天的对话。

17
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:43,880
Hey, Michelle.
嘿，Michelle。

18
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:50,920
Good to see you.
很高兴见到你。

19
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:51,920
Are you at lunch?
你在吃午饭吗？

20
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:52,920
Oh, hi, Jim.
哦，嗨，Jim。

21
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:54,760
No, I just got back.
不，我刚回来。

22
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,480
I thought you were on vacation now.
我以为你现在在度假呢。

23
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:58,400
No, I wish I was.
不，我倒希望是。

24
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,760
I just got back from Spain, actually.
实际上，我刚从西班牙回来。

25
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:02,280
Oh, wonderful.
哦，太棒了。

26
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:04,980
Have you been there before or was it your first time?
你以前去过那里，还是这是第一次？

27
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:05,980
My first time.
第一次。

28
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:09,000
I've traveled around Europe a lot, but this was my first time to Spain.
我去过欧洲很多地方，但这是第一次去西班牙。

29
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,520
It was amazing and the weather was just beautiful.
太棒了，天气也非常好。

30
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:14,280
No rain and just sun, sun, sun.
没有下雨，只有阳光、阳光、阳光。

31
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:16,280
I'm so jealous of you.
我真羡慕你。

32
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:18,560
I've never been anywhere in Europe.
我从来没去过欧洲任何地方。

33
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:21,760
I've always dreamed of traveling around and seeing the sights.
我一直梦想着到处旅行，看看风景。

34
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:23,960
Well, I really recommend Spain.
嗯，我强烈推荐西班牙。

35
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:25,560
You really should go.
你真应该去。

36
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:29,000
Anyway, it's been great to catch up, but I must be going.
总之，很高兴能聊一聊，但我得走了。

37
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,240
This is my floor.
我到这层了。

38
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:31,480
Speak again soon, I hope.
希望很快再聊。

39
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,480
For sure.
当然。

40
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:33,480
Take care.
保重。

41
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,480
All right.
好的。

42
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,480
We're back.
我们回来了。

43
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:42,360
So, now, let's take a look at some of the language on Language Takeaway.
那么，现在让我们看看“语言要点”部分的一些语言点。

44
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,360
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

45
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,360
All right.
好的。

46
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:47,520
In Language Takeaway, we've got a couple of words and phrases for you.
在“语言要点”中，我们为大家准备了一些单词和短语。

47
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,560
The first one is, I just got back.
第一个是“I just got back”。

48
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:53,320
So, to get back from somewhere, Marco.
所以，“to get back from somewhere”，Marco。

49
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:54,480
That's right, Jim.
没错，Jim。

50
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,640
Just got back from Europe.
刚从欧洲回来。

51
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:04,720
And when you say, I just got back, is I recently or very recently returned from somewhere.
当你说“I just got back”时，意思是我最近或刚刚从某个地方回来。

52
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:05,720
That's right.
没错。

53
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:08,320
To get back from somewhere means to return from that place.
“To get back from somewhere”意思是回到那个地方。

54
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:12,680
So, in this dialogue, Jim just got back from Spain.
所以，在这个对话中，Jim刚从西班牙回来。

55
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:15,000
Michelle just got back from lunch.
Michelle刚吃完午饭回来。

56
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,040
This means to return from somewhere.
这意思是回到某个地方。

57
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,040
That's right.
没错。

58
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:22,320
So, it can be a place, not only a country, but it can be, for example, the office.
所以，它可以是一个地方，不只是一个国家，比如也可以是办公室。

59
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:24,760
I just got back from work.
我刚下班回来。

60
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:27,360
Or I just got back from football practice.
或者我刚从足球训练回来。

61
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,760
That's why I'm very sweaty.
所以我浑身是汗。

62
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,760
Right.
对。

63
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:34,000
So, this obviously means that you are now not in the same place where you just got back
所以，这显然意味着你现在不在你刚回来的那个地方。

64
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
from.


65
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
No, I'm from America.
不，我来自美国。

66
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,560
I went to Spain on vacation and I just got back from Spain.
我去西班牙度假，然后刚从西班牙回来。

67
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,280
That means I'm in America again.
这意味着我又在美国了。

68
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,280
Yeah, exactly.
是的，没错。

69
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,600
You're not still in Spain.
你不在西班牙了。

70
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,600
No.
不在了。

71
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,600
All right.
好的。

72
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,800
So, that's for our first word.
这就是我们的第一个词。

73
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,280
Now, let's go on.
现在，我们继续。

74
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:52,720
And Michelle said, oh, I'm so jealous of you.
Michelle说：“哦，我真羡慕你。”

75
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:53,720
All right.
好的。

76
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:56,000
Jealous is an adjective and a very, very common one.
“Jealous”是一个形容词，非常非常常见。

77
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
You can use it in many different circumstances.
你可以在很多不同的情况下使用它。

78
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,200
It means to want what someone else has.
它的意思是想要别人拥有的东西。

79
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,200
That's right.
没错。

80
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:05,640
So, in this case, Michelle is jealous that Jim went on vacation.
所以，在这个例子中，Michelle羡慕Jim去度假了。

81
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:08,160
So, she wishes she could go on vacation.
所以，她希望自己能去度假。

82
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:09,160
That's right.
没错。

83
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:10,160
I'm so jealous of you.
我真羡慕你。

84
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:14,080
Or if you see someone who has a new pair of shoes and you like the shoes because you don't
或者，如果你看到有人有双新鞋，你喜欢那双鞋，因为你自己没有，

85
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:16,600
have them, you can say, I'm so jealous.
你可以说，我真羡慕。

86
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,960
I love your shoes.
我喜欢你的鞋子。

87
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:18,960
That's right.
没错。

88
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,920
And if you're jealous, you say, I am jealous.
如果你感到嫉妒，你就说，我嫉妒。

89
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:25,800
Or if you're jealous of a person, you say, I am jealous of you.
或者，如果你嫉妒某个人，你就说，我嫉妒你。

90
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,920
And so, they were ending their conversation and Jim said, you know what?
然后，他们结束了对话，吉姆说，你知道吗？

91
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:31,760
It's been great to catch up with you.
跟你叙叙旧真是太好了。

92
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:32,760
All right.
好的。

93
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:35,320
This is a really important phrase, to catch up.
这是一个非常重要的短语，“叙旧”。

94
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,480
It means two different things.
它有两种不同的意思。

95
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:39,080
And we're going to talk about one meaning here today.
我们今天要讨论其中一种意思。

96
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:43,280
To catch up with someone, like to talk to them about what they've been doing recently,
“和某人叙旧”，比如和他们聊聊他们最近在做什么，

97
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:48,120
means to learn about their life because maybe you haven't talked in a long time.
意思是了解他们的生活，因为可能你们很久没说话了。

98
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,120
That's right.
没错。

99
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:54,240
So, maybe you haven't seen your friend in two years and you go out for dinner to catch
所以，也许你两年没见朋友了，你们出去吃饭叙旧，

100
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:58,960
up, to talk about what has happened in your life recently.
聊聊你们最近生活中发生了什么。

101
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,960
That's right.
没错。

102
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:03,600
Or if you see a friend on the street and you know that you haven't seen him or her in a
或者，如果你在街上遇到一个朋友，并且你知道你已经很久没见到他或她了，

103
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:06,640
long time, you can make a date to catch up.
你可以约个时间叙叙旧。

104
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:09,680
So, hey Marco, I haven't seen you in months.
所以，嘿，Marco，我好几个月没见到你了。

105
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,340
Let's catch up sometime soon.
我们找个时间聚聚吧。

106
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:12,340
That's right.
没错。

107
00:04:12,340 --> 00:04:16,520
And that means to share information and to find out how you have been recently.
这意味着分享信息，了解你最近过得怎么样。

108
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:17,520
Exactly.
正是如此。

109
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:18,520
All right.
好的。

110
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:22,280
Now, when he was getting out of the elevator, he said, this is my floor.
现在，当他走出电梯时，他说，这是我到的楼层。

111
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:24,800
Now, we know floor, but my floor, what is this?
我们知道“楼层”这个词，但“我的楼层”是什么意思？

112
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,800
My floor, your floor, whose floor?
我的楼层，你的楼层，谁的楼层？

113
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,800
Right.
对。

114
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,800
This doesn't make much sense, does it?
这听起来不太合理，对吧？

115
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:34,360
Well, actually floor here means that this is the floor that I work on or the floor that
嗯，实际上这里的“楼层”指的是我工作的楼层或者

116
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,360
I live on.
我住的楼层。

117
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,920
It means the place I'm going to.
它指的是我要去的地方。

118
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:37,920
Right.
对。

119
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:42,560
So, we know floor, the ground beneath our feet in a building.
所以，我们知道“楼层”是指建筑物里脚下的地面。

120
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:46,200
But in this case, we're talking about one of the levels of a building.
但在这个例子中，我们指的是建筑物的其中一层。

121
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,080
So, maybe the sixth floor.
那么，可能是六楼吧。

122
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,080
That's right.
没错。

123
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:54,320
So, if I'm in my apartment building in the elevator, I can say, oh, stop the elevator.
所以，如果我在公寓楼的电梯里，我可以说，哦，停一下电梯。

124
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,320
This is my floor.
这是我住的楼层。

125
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:57,360
I want to get off the elevator.
我想下电梯。

126
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,360
Right.
对。

127
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,360
This is where I live.
这就是我住的地方。

128
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,360
All right.
好的。

129
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,800
So, a lot of great stuff there.
那里有很多好东西。

130
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:05,240
Why don't we take a break and listen to the dialogue again?
我们休息一下，再听一遍对话怎么样？

131
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:08,520
Hey, Michelle.
嘿，米歇尔。

132
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:15,200
Good to see you.
很高兴见到你。

133
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,200
Are you at lunch?
你在吃午饭吗？

134
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,200
Oh, hi, Jim.
哦，嗨，吉姆。

135
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,000
No, I just got back.
不，我刚回来。

136
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,800
I thought you were on vacation now.
我以为你现在在度假呢。

137
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,640
No, I wish I was.
不，我倒希望是。

138
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:25,000
I just got back from Spain, actually.
实际上，我刚从西班牙回来。

139
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,520
Oh, wonderful.
哦，太棒了。

140
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:29,220
Have you been there before or was it your first time?
你以前去过那里，还是这是第一次？

141
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:30,220
My first time.
我的第一次。

142
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:33,240
I've traveled around Europe a lot, but this is my first time to Spain.
我去过欧洲很多地方，但这是第一次来西班牙。

143
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,760
It was amazing and the weather was just beautiful.
太棒了，天气也特别好。

144
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:38,520
No rain and just sun, sun, sun.
没下雨，全是太阳、太阳、太阳。

145
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,360
I'm so jealous of you.
我真羡慕你。

146
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,800
I've never been anywhere in Europe.
我从来没去过欧洲任何地方。

147
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:46,000
I've always dreamed of traveling around and seeing the sights.
我一直梦想着到处旅行，看看风景。

148
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,200
Well, I really recommend Spain.
嗯，我强烈推荐西班牙。

149
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,600
You really should go.
你真应该去。

150
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:53,240
Anyway, it's been great to catch up, but I must be going.
总之，很高兴能聊聊，但我得走了。

151
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,480
This is my floor.
我到这层了。

152
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,720
Speak again soon, I hope.
希望很快再聊。

153
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,720
For sure.
当然。

154
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,720
Take care.
保重。

155
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:00,160
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

156
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:06,720
So, now let's take a look at four key phrases on Fluency Builder.
那么，现在来看看“流利度构建器”里的四个关键短语。

157
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,960
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

158
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:13,160
So, there are some keys to these small talk conversations and they are definitely the
所以，这些闲聊对话有一些关键点，它们绝对是

159
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,160
phrases.
短语。

160
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:16,480
The first one we have here is, good to see you.
我们这里的第一个是，很高兴见到你。

161
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:19,320
So, Jim says, hey, Michelle, good to see you.
所以，吉姆说，嘿，米歇尔，很高兴见到你。

162
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,320
That's right.
没错。

163
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:25,520
So, we've chosen this phrase because it's very casual and very common to use as a polite
我们选择这个短语是因为它非常随意，而且常用作一种礼貌的

164
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:27,520
way of saying, hey, how are you?
方式来说“嘿，你好吗？”

165
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,520
Good to see you.
很高兴见到你。

166
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:32,480
I'm actually showing you that I'm happy that I am talking to you.
我其实是在向你表示，我很高兴能和你说话。

167
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,920
So, this is a very flexible phrase.
所以，这是一个非常灵活的短语。

168
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:38,840
You can say it at the beginning of a conversation when you just see someone, hey, Marco, good
你可以在对话开始时刚见到某人时说，嘿，马可，很高兴

169
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:39,840
to see you.
见到你。

170
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,720
Or at the end, you can say, it was very good to see you.
或者在结束时，你可以说，很高兴见到你。

171
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,120
I hope to see you again soon.
希望很快能再见到你。

172
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,120
That's right.
没错。

173
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:51,160
So, maybe you can use it at the beginning if you just begin to talk to someone or if
所以，你可以在刚开始和别人说话时用它，或者

174
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,200
you're saying goodbye, you can say, well, you know what?
在告别时，你可以说，嗯，你知道吗？

175
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,960
I have to go now, but it's been good to see you.
我现在得走了，但很高兴见到你。

176
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,880
So, very flexible phrase.
所以，这是一个非常灵活的短语。

177
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:58,880
That's right.
没错。

178
00:06:58,880 --> 00:06:59,880
That's right.
没错。

179
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:03,880
Now, when Michelle thought that Jim was on vacation, Jim said, no, no, no.
现在，当米歇尔以为吉姆在度假时，吉姆说，不，不，不。

180
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,840
I wish I was.
我希望我是。

181
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:06,840
All right.
好吧。

182
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,840
I wish I was.
我希望我是。

183
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,920
I thought you were on vacation.
我以为你在度假。

184
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:14,040
So, she thought that he was still on vacation in Spain.
所以，她以为他还在西班牙度假。

185
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:18,680
And he says, well, I'm not because, you know, here I am, but I wish I was.
然后他说，嗯，我不是，因为，你知道，我在这儿，但我希望我是。

186
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:22,800
I wish I was in Spain right now because Spain is so nice.
我希望我现在在西班牙，因为西班牙太美了。

187
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,800
That's right.
没错。

188
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:28,920
So, it may seem a little bit strange, but it's actually completing the idea.
所以，这可能看起来有点奇怪，但实际上是在补充完整这个想法。

189
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:32,680
And basically, we're using the verb to be because that's the question.
基本上，我们用了动词“是”，因为那是问题所在。

190
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,080
Are you on vacation?
你在度假吗？

191
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:37,280
No, I wish I was on vacation.
不，我希望我在度假。

192
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:40,040
So, that means he's not, but he wants to be.
所以，这意味着他不是，但他想是。

193
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,040
That's right.
没错。

194
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:46,560
Okay, so now, he actually had to get going and he used this exact phrase.
好的，那么现在，他实际上得走了，他用了这个确切的短语。

195
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:49,360
He said, I must be going.
他说，我必须走了。

196
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,360
I must be going.
我必须走了。

197
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,920
Now, remember this as a phrase.
现在，记住这是一个短语。

198
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:54,400
This is a good way to end a conversation.
这是结束对话的好方法。

199
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:55,960
Maybe you have to go to work.
也许你得去上班。

200
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:57,500
Maybe you have your kids at home.
也许你的孩子在家。

201
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,760
You have to take them somewhere.
你得带他们去某个地方。

202
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:03,920
So, you say, I'm really sorry, I must be going, but let's see each other again soon.
所以，你说，真的很抱歉，我必须走了，但我们很快再见面吧。

203
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,920
That's right.
没错。

204
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,760
So, you are politely ending the conversation.
所以，你是在礼貌地结束对话。

205
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:09,840
You are politely saying, I can't talk to you anymore.
你是在礼貌地说，我不能再和你聊了。

206
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:13,480
I must be going now, but it's been great to talk to you.
我现在必须走了，但和你聊天很开心。

207
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,480
That's right.
没错。

208
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,480
Very polite.
非常礼貌。

209
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,480
So, remember this one.
所以，记住这个。

210
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,480
It's better than, I'm going now.
这比说“我现在走了”要好。

211
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,480
We don't say that.
我们不会那么说。

212
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,480
Yeah, or I have to go.
是的，或者“我得走了”。

213
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:22,720
Well, you can say, I have to go, but it's nice saying, oh, you know what?
嗯，你可以说“我得走了”，但说“哦，你知道吗？”更好。

214
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:26,600
I really like talking to you, but I must be going now.
我真的很喜欢和你聊天，但我现在必须走了。

215
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:29,840
And Jim also finished by saying, we'll speak again soon.
吉姆最后还说，我们很快再聊。

216
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:32,120
And Michelle said, for sure.
米歇尔说，当然。

217
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,120
For sure.
当然。

218
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:36,520
Now, Americans particularly love to say this phrase.
现在，美国人特别喜欢说这个短语。

219
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:40,560
For sure means yes, or I agree, or definitely.
“当然”意思是“是的”，或者“我同意”，或者“肯定”。

220
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:41,560
Right.
对。

221
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,200
You can use it as an interjection.
你可以把它用作感叹词。

222
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:47,440
So, if I say, hey, Catherine, am I going to see you later on today?
所以，如果我说，嘿，凯瑟琳，我今天晚些时候会见到你吗？

223
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,440
Yeah, for sure.
是的，当然。

224
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,440
For sure.
当然。

225
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,440
There we go.
就是这样。

226
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:53,560
So, you're saying yes, absolutely, definitely, for sure.
所以，你是在说“是的，绝对，肯定，当然”。

227
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:55,640
So, Marco, my birthday is Friday night.
所以，马可，我的生日是周五晚上。

228
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,200
Are you going to come to the party?
你会来参加派对吗？

229
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,200
For sure.
当然。

230
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,200
I wouldn't miss it for the world.
我绝不会错过。

231
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,200
All right.
好吧。

232
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,760
So, that's all we have for today.
所以，这就是我们今天的内容。

233
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:07,080
Why don't we review everything we've taken a look at now and listen to the dialogue one
我们为什么不回顾一下我们看过的所有内容，然后最后再听一遍对话

234
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,840
last time.
呢？

235
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:12,000
Hey, Michelle.
嘿，米歇尔。

236
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:18,840
Good to see you.
很高兴见到你。

237
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,840
Are you at lunch?
你在吃午饭吗？

238
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,840
Oh, hi, Jim.
哦，嗨，吉姆。

239
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,640
No, I just got back.
不，我刚回来。

240
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,360
I thought you were on vacation now.
我以为你现在在度假。

241
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,280
No, I wish I was.
不，我倒希望我是。

242
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,760
I just got back from Spain, actually.
其实我刚从西班牙回来。

243
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,160
Oh, wonderful.
哦，真棒。

244
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,880
Have you been there before or was it your first time?
你以前去过那里，还是这是第一次？

245
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:33,880
My first time.
第一次。

246
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:36,880
I've traveled around Europe a lot, but this was my first time to Spain.
我去过欧洲很多地方，但这是第一次去西班牙。

247
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:39,400
It was amazing and the weather was just beautiful.
太棒了，天气也特别好。

248
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,160
No rain and just sun, sun, sun.
没下雨，全是太阳、太阳、太阳。

249
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,040
I'm so jealous of you.
我真羡慕你。

250
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:46,440
I've never been anywhere in Europe.
我从来没去过欧洲任何地方。

251
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:49,640
I've always dreamed of traveling around and seeing the sights.
我一直梦想着到处旅行，看看风景。

252
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,840
Well, I really recommend Spain.
嗯，我强烈推荐西班牙。

253
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,440
You really should go.
你真该去一趟。

254
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:56,840
Anyway, it's been great to catch up, but I must be going.
总之，很高兴能聊一聊，但我得走了。

255
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,080
This is my floor.
我到这层了。

256
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,320
Speak again soon, I hope.
希望很快再聊。

257
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,320
For sure.
当然。

258
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,320
Take care.
保重。

259
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,320
All right.
好的。

260
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:06,560
So, this was another part of our small talk series.
所以，这是我们闲聊系列的另一部分。

261
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:13,300
As you can see, very short, but very useful language used to talk very briefly with someone.
如你所见，非常简短，但用来跟人简短交谈非常有用。

262
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:14,300
It always happens.
这种事经常发生。

263
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:18,520
You meet somebody at the elevator or you just want to talk very quickly.
你在电梯里遇到某人，或者只想快速聊几句。

264
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:23,920
Yeah, but you don't want to talk about anything that's too personal like someone's politics
是啊，但你不想谈太私人的话题，比如某人的政治观点。

265
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:28,720
or their religious beliefs or their children because maybe you don't know them very well.
或者他们的宗教信仰、孩子，因为可能你跟他们不太熟。

266
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:35,960
So, these are really great topics to talk about like business trips or vacation or the
所以，这些是很棒的话题，比如商务旅行、度假。

267
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,720
weather.
或者天气。

268
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:41,400
English speakers love to talk about these when they don't know someone that well.
英语母语者在跟不太熟的人聊天时喜欢谈这些。

269
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,400
That's right.
没错。

270
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,400
That's right.
没错。

271
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:46,560
So, if you have any questions or any comments about this lesson or you want to suggest any
所以，如果你对这课有任何问题或评论，或者想建议其他话题。

272
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:49,960
other topics, you can find us at EnglishPod.com.
你可以在EnglishPod.com找到我们。

273
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:50,960
We hope to see you all there.
希望在那里见到大家。

274
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:51,960
Bye.
再见。

275
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
See you guys.
各位再见。

276
00:10:52,960 --> 00:11:21,060
I will see you guys later, take care.
回头见，保重。
